The paper discusses the use of machine learning and data science techniques for analyzing data from bio-loggers, which involves processing sensor data from animals in their natural habitats. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of Computer Science that deal with machine learning and data science. Specifically, the use of matrix factorization and topic modeling suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the use of accelerometer data suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), which deal with image and signal processing and social network analysis, respectively.
